522:               /************************************************************************
523:               DataEEInit
524:               
525:               This routine finds an unexpired page to become an active page. It then
526:               counts the number of active pages. If no active pages are found, the
527:               first unexpired page is initialized for emulation. If one active page is
528:               found, it is assumes a reset occurred and the function does nothing. If
529:               two active pages are found, it is assumes a reset occurred during a pack.
530:               The second page is erased and a pack is called. If three, an error code
531:               is returned as the allocated memory is assumed to be corrupted. This
532:               function must be called prior to any other operation.
533:               
534:               Parameters:		None
535:               Return:			Status value (0 for pass)
536:               Side Effects:	Data EE flags may be updated.
