741:               and an error code is returned. A read is performed, if the data was not
742:               changed, the function exits. If the last location is programmed, the Pack
743:               Skipped error flag is set (one location should always be available). The
744:               data EE information (MSB = address, LSW = data) is programmed and
745:               verified. If the verify fails, the Write Error flag is set. If the write
746:               went into the last location of the page, pack is called. This function
747:               can be called by the user.
